C'mon, C'mon is the fourth studio album by American singer-songwriter Sheryl Crow
released on April 8, 2002 in the United Kingdom and April 16, 2002 in the United
States. Lead single "Soak Up the Sun" peaked at #1 on the Billboard Adult Contemporary
chart and #17 on the Billboard Hot 100, becoming one of her biggest hits since
"All I Wanna Do". The album was arguably her most pop-influenced to date, a big
departure from the folk and experimental influences on her previous release
Globe Sessions.
